title: Atlas Iron lifts prices, iron ore shipped
text:
Thu, Sep 10, 2015, 9:09 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 51 mins. Atlas Iron lifts prices, iron ore shipped AAP – 10 minutes ago Print 
A small recovery in iron ore prices has helped boost margins and prices for struggling junior miner Atlas Iron. 
Atlas says that while its cash costs rose slightly to $56.52 per wet metric tonne in August, margins were higher thanks to its iron ore sale price rising by $4 to $61/WMT. 
The miner, which suffered a $1.4 billion annual loss in 2014/15, also lifted the amount of iron ore it shipped by 33 per cent to 1.18WMT. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Unemployment rate tipped to ease AAP
